title: Linkin Park - 08.24.2012 - Tinley Park, IL
description:
Date: August 24, 2012 	  	
Tour: Honda Civic Tour
Show #: 9 of 17
Location: Tinley Park, Illinois 	  	
Venue: First Midwest Bank Amphitheater 	  		  	  	 	

Setlist: 	
01. A Place For My Head (Long Intro; Ext. Outro)
02. Given Up (Ext. Outro w/ Extra Note)
03. New Divide 	
04. With You (2012 Ext. Intro; Ext. Scratch Outro)
05. VICTIMIZED (w/ QWERTY) 
	
07. Empty Spaces 	
08. When They Come For Me 	
09. LIES GREED MISERY 
	 	
11. Waiting For The End (Apaches Intro w/ 'Until It Breaks' rap; Ext. Outro)
 	
13. LOATR/SOTD/Iridescent (Ballad Medley)
14. The Catalyst 	
15. LOST IN THE ECHO (2012 Intro)
16. Numb (Outro 'Numb/Encore' lyrics tease (Mike))
17. What I've Done 	
18. BURN IT DOWN
 		
20. Bleed It Out (Ext. Bridge w/ Beastie Boys 'Sabotage'; Ext. Outro)
----------------------------------------------------
21. TINFOIL 	
22. Faint (Ext. Outro)
23. Lying From You / Papercut (Medley)
24. One Step Closer (Ext. Outro)
  	 
  	 
Show Notes:
- The setlist had a few songs in different spots than the last time it was played in Alpharetta, GA. Alpharetta's songs four through eight were: 'Somewhere I Belong', 'Empty Spaces', 'When They Come For Me', 'VICTIMIZED (w/ QWERTY)', and 'With You'. The order at this show was: 'With You', 'VICTIMIZED (w/ QWERTY)', 'Somewhere I Belong', 'Empty Spaces', and 'When They Come For Me'.
- Mike rapped a verse from 'Until It Breaks' over the intro to 'Waiting For The End'.
- Mike sang part of the lyrics to 'Numb/Encore' over the outro of 'Numb'.
- 'Bleed It Out' featured the Beastie Boys' 'Sabotage' bridge.
 
 
Other Notes:
- On August 16, 2012, five shows on the Honda Civic Tour were removed from the DSP website (Wantagh, Noblesville, Tinley Park, Mountain View, and Carson). While Noblesville was randomly released mid-tour, the other four were never released due to disagreements with the venues on how much money they should get from the sale of each recording.
